data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now takes `Func<>`, not `Expression<Func<>>`

Your expression-tree construction **won't compile** anymore. The fix is dramatically simpler ŌĆö just use a regular lambda with `if`:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

Delete all the `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` / `Expression.Parameter` code.

---

### 2. Complex type columns ŌĆö two changes

**a) Column name uniquification:** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared a column silently (data corruption risk). EF 10 appends a numeric suffix to disambiguate. If you intentionally want shared columns, pin them explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use full path:** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was previously mapped to column `BillingAddress_City`. EF 10 maps it to `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To preserve the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

> **Both of these will generate migrations that rename columns**, which can break existing databases if not handled carefully. Run `dotnet ef migrations add` and inspect the output.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Apply the same change to `CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, `CommandScalarExecuted`, `CommandNonQueryExecuting`, `CommandNonQueryExecuted`, etc.
